Spermatheca — Calyx very long 60 snake-shaped, atrium incorporated in the calyx whose walls are thickened at the anterior tip, calyx gets Λ-shaped one-fourths of its length towards vesicle, minor duct not visible (
Figure 1C
).

Chelicera — Fixed digit 32 (28–38) and movable digit 27 (25–30) long with two widely separated teeth (
Figure 2D
).

